          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1661183668402-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1661183668402-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a knob of<strong> butter alternative </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble your<strong> portobello mushroom[s]</strong> roughly into the pan with your hands</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and the <strong>crushed walnuts</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>2-3 min or until the mushroom has started to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1661183670994-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1661183670994-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1661183670994-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1661183670994-x1000.jpg",
